  "texts": [
    "Performance ComparisonIn experiments, three baseline models are compared to TP-GPT using TransQuery benchmark that has 50 complex transportation problems.",
    "As shown in Table III, TP-GPT significantly outperforms other baseline models on TransQuery with an average performance score of 0.87, surpassing GPT-4 Turbo of 0.57, PaLM 2 of 0.34, and SQLCoder of 0.16.",
    "Specifically, out of total 50 questions, TP-GPT generates 40 flawless responses accounting for 80% of the whole dataset, 7 runnable queries but imperfect responses, and only 3 nonfunctional queries.",
    "Whereas, the state-of-the-art LLM GPT-4 Turbo only generates 22 flawless responses accounting for 44% of the whole dataset, even with superior pre-trained reasoning and contextual capability.",
    "PaLM 2 and SQLCoder barely generate 15 and 7 flawless responses accounting for the percentage of 30% and 14% respectively.TABLE III: Performance comparison of TP-GPT with baseline models on TransQuery traffic-analysis benchmark Model Response Metrics Avg."
  ],
